by Synne Industries » Mon Jan 11, 2021 8:05 am

AAAN: The Garden is a strange place to say the least. It is an isolated spacetime pocket “anchored” to a 20x20 meter space somewhere in Yangon, Earth. The Garden itself is subject to fluctuations in local physics, energy, and dimensionality though seems to have at least some limits as seen with the temperatures (at least the recorded ones) not dipping below absolute zero. The natural blue tint also implies that the color resulting from certain photon wavelengths can be freely altered without any adverse effects on “adjacent physics”, either that or it is simply the human (or sometimes inhuman) perception of color that is affected. As space is constantly in a flux as a result of new objects and places being created or removed, there is no true way to map things in a traditional sense and any navigation is limited to marking one’s rough position in relation to Holly’s Treehouse.

AAN: Radiant Systems was one of the first, actually, the first AG team, developing AG technologies for commercial purposes. Even after a move from their origin country to Japan, they still retain a benevolent stance in regards to what they produce, hoping their AG tech can help benefit humanity as a whole.

Ninja’d

AN: Talers are Waisnor‘s unique type of currency. They come in both coins and banknotes with the former only going down to as low as intervals of 0.5 Talers but going as high as 5 Taler coins. The banknotes depict famous people of Waisnor and their works ranging from poets to Olympic champions to aircraft designers.
